<section id="command-pitch">
    <title>PITCH</title>

<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term>Synopsis</term>
<listitem>
<synopsis><command>PITCH</command></synopsis>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Description</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Outputs the angle of the turtle's pitch in degrees.
It is important to <link linkend="understand-your-orientation-in-3D">understand your orientation in 3D</link>.
See also <link linkend="command-setpitch">SETPITCH</link>.
</para>
<para>
This command is designed to run in <link linkend="command-perspective">PERSPECTIVE</link> mode.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Example</term>
<listitem>
    <programlisting><userinput>SETPITCH 90
SHOW PITCH</userinput>
90
</programlisting>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>

</section>
